An Indian Government initiative, Ayurveda, Yoga and Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha, and Homeopathy (AYUSH) held by the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, 2014 provides education, awareness, and enhances research to use natural resources that can fight several life threatening diseases. Ayurvedic medicine has been in use since two thousand years. Over 700 herbal drugs were recorded in Ayurveda with reported clinical effects categorised into 50 drug classifications. Also, Unani is recognized as traditional medicine producer, showing therapeutic effects against many infectious diseases. Both the Ayurvedic and Unani systems of medicine have recorded several preparations like decoctions, powders, and liquids of potential plants with immunomodulatory and antiviral properties (
 Subhose et al., 2005; 
 Patwardhan et al., 2005; 
 Weeks, 2020).
